FBIS4-49377 "drchi088_a_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-088 Daily Report 6 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Government Signs WIPO Trademark Agreement Government Signs WIPO Trademark Agreement OW0605045794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0439 GMT 6 May 94 OW0605045794 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Geneva, May 5 (XINHUA) -- China joined the Nice agreement of the World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO) on Thursday [5 May] to internationalize its trademark system. The agreement, known as "The Agreement on the International Classification of Goods and Services for Trademark Registration," was first established in 1957 and is the major instrument of WIPO. Tang Yufeng, deputy representative of the Chinese mission to the UN in Geneva, presented a protocol for entry to Arpad Bogsch, director-general of WIPO. Since joining WIPO in 1980, China has signed nearly all international agreements protecting intellectual property rights. Bogsch said that a special meeting will be held for the entry of Chinese products into international trademark registration. The Nice agreement now has 36 signatory members.
